  m_Name: Fibula_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Fibula_L
  partName: Fibula Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left fibula is a long, slender bone located along the lateral side of the
    canine hindlimb beside the tibia. Although it bears less weight than the tibia,
    the fibula serves as an important attachment site for muscles and ligaments controlling
    hindlimb movement. It contributes to stabilization of the stifle and hock joints
  - while supporting coordinated locomotion. The bone also assists in maintaining
    proper alignment and structural integrity of the lower hindlimb. Muscles associated
    with the fibula play essential roles in paw movement and balance during activity.
